ugh the human HBV receptor sodium taurocholate cotransporting polypeptide but could not be neutralized by sera from vaccinated humans. Antihepadnaviral treatment using an approved reverse transcriptase inhibitor blocked replication of all bat hepadnaviruses. Our data suggest that bats may have been ancestral sources of primate hepadnaviruses. The observed zoonotic potential might affect concepts aimed at eradicating HBV.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Drexler, J. F.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Geipel, A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Konig, A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Corman, V. M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "van Riel, D.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Leijten, L. M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bremer, C. M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Rasche, A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Cottontail, V. M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Maganga, G. D.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Schlegel, M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Muller, M. A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Adam, A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Klose, S. M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Carneiro, A. J.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Stocker, A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Franke, C. R.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Gloza-Rausch, F.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Geyer, J.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Annan, A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Adu-Sarkodie, Y.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Oppong, S.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Binger, T.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Vallo, P.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tschapka, M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ulrich, R. G.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Gerlich, W. H.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Leroy, E.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kuiken, T.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Glebe, D.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Drosten, C.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Animals", "Base Sequence", "Cell Line, Tumor", "Chiroptera/*vir